============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Determinism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   All events are causally determined by prior events and natural laws
Philosopher:  Laplace/Spinoza
Example:      If universe were rewound exactly, every event would repeat identically

Concept:      Phenomenology
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Philosophy must study first-person conscious experience directly
Philosopher:  Husserl/Heidegger
Example:      What is the structure of my experience of time or other people?

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

============================================================
  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Charles Darwin
Lived:         1809 - 1882
Nationality:   English
Field:         Biology
Known For:     Evolution by Natural Selection
Contribution:  On the Origin of Species; explained diversity of life on Earth
Quote:         "It is not the strongest that survives, but the most adaptable."

Name:          Albert Einstein
Lived:         1879 - 1955
Nationality:   German-American
Field:         Physics
Known For:     Theory of Relativity
Contribution:  E=mc2; photoelectric effect; special and general relativity
Quote:         "Imagination is more important than knowledge."

Name:          Abraham Lincoln
Lived:         1809 - 1865
Nationality:   American
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Emancipation Proclamation
Contribution:  16th US President; preserved Union; abolished slavery; Gettysburg Address
Quote:         "Government of the people, by the people, for the people."

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Central Bank
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government institution managing currency, money supply, interest rates
Formula:    Taylor Rule for interest rates
Economist:  John Taylor
Example:    US Federal Reserve raised rates to 5.25% in 2023 to fight inflation

Concept:    Inflation
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: General rise in price levels eroding purchasing power
Formula:    Inflation = (CPI_t - CPI_t-1)/CPI_t-1 x 100
Economist:  Irving Fisher
Example:    2022 US inflation hit 9.1%; Fed raised rates to combat it

Concept:    Moral Hazard
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Entity takes more risk when not bearing full consequences
Formula:    Conceptual
Economist:  Adam Smith/Pauly
Example:    Banks took excessive risks knowing government would bail them out 2008

